The paper discusses research on advanced and efficient methods for the recognition of complex events in large, heterogeneous and interdependent data streams. This involves multiple aspects such as efficient detection of patterns, handling uncertainty and noise, and machine learning techniques for inferring interesting patterns. These topics are closely related to the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), data science (cs.DS), software engineering (cs.SE), and databases (cs.DB). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely.
